title: N.J. Sports Now: Underdog Yankees deserve to celebrate (VIDEO)
text:
Comments When the 2015 season started, expectations for the Yankees were low. How low? Not one of MLB Network Radio's experts picked the team with the highest payroll in the American League to qualify for the postseason. Here they are, the 2015 MLB Network Radio Analyst Predictions. Big year if you're a #Nationals or #Ma — MLB Network Radio (@MLBNetworkRadio) April 3, 2015 
Sure, if everything went right, they had a chance —in theory. But, as with every season and every team, it didn't. Despite who the Yankees are, the name-brand talent they have and past expectations, this wasn't supposed to be a playoff team. When you add up the circumstances against them, they were an underdog. 
That's what made the reaction to their postseason-clinching celebration so odd last night. Why are the @Yankees celebrating like they won the division.You're in a one game playoff. You aren't REALLY in the playoffs yet #yankeessuck — Joe LaBarre (@joe_labarre) October 2, 2015 Remember when the Yankees would clinch the division and there was NO celebrating because their mission wasn't accomplished yet? #GloryYears
